  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Melee Tactics Toolbox pg. 19</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 1 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 1 lb.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> B; <strong>Special</strong> disarm</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Light; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Flails</p><h3>Description</h3><p>One end of this short rope has a sling bullet wrapped in a monkey's fist knot, and the other end is tied in a small loop. You wrap the loop around your wrist as a full-round action and swing the weighted end like a flail. If the loop is properly attached to your wrist and you drop the rope-shot or are disarmed, you can recover it as a swift action. Removing the weapon's loop is a full-round action. You get a +2 bonus on Sleight of Hand checks made to conceal a rope-shot on your body. Halflings treat rope-shots as martial weapons.</p>"
